# Deployment

The system runs as a set of containers on a private docker network.

## Containers (this repo)

| Service          | Image source             | Purpose                                                  |
|------------------|--------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| `frontend`       | `frontend/Dockerfile`    | Next.js dashboard, served by Node                        |
| `backend`        | `backend/Dockerfile`     | FastAPI: `/api/{trades,strategies,signals,backtests,system}` |
| `trading-engine` | `Dockerfile` (root)      | Strategy + risk + execution loop                         |
| `duckdb`         | sidecar volume + service | Persists `/data/market.duckdb` and parquet snapshots     |
| `redis`          | `redis:7-alpine`         | Pub/sub between engine, backend, and monitoring          |

## Containers (external, already running)

| Service  | Notes                                          |
|----------|------------------------------------------------|
| `ollama` | Local LLM runtime, used by `research.llm`      |
| `hermes` | Internal helper service                        |

## Network

All services join the `trading-net` docker network. `docker-compose.yml`
declares it with `external: true` for `ollama` / `hermes` so they can be
managed independently.

## Hostnames

Services address each other by container name:

- backend → `redis`, `duckdb`, `ollama`, `hermes`
- frontend → `backend`
- trading-engine → `redis`, `duckdb`, `backend`

Never use `localhost` inside containers; always use the service name.

## Environment

- `ENV=dev|staging|prod` is required and printed at boot.
- Health endpoints: `backend` exposes `GET /api/system/health` returning
  `{status, version, uptime_s, db_ok, redis_ok}`.

## Build and run

```bash
docker compose build
docker compose up -d
docker compose logs -f trading-engine
```

CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) builds every image on PR; merges to `main`
push images to the registry.
